21/09/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Representatives of the ruling Socialist Party and the main opposition Democratic Party met on Monday (20 September) with the head of the OSCE Presence in Albania, Osmo Lipponen. They discussed ways to resolve the deadlock that has developed among members of the bipartisan commission on electoral reform. The commission, established in July, has been unable to reach consensus on major issues. 
In other news, the government announced that the World Bank has agreed to provide financing for a 3m-euro environmental project in Albania. It envisions the construction of a site to accommodate waste from a former chemical plant in Porto Romano, on the Adriatic coast. (Albanian Daily News - 21/09/04; ATA - 20/09/04) 
